#: ../../../terminal-compatibility.rst:308
msgid "DCS commands and GNU screen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../terminal-compatibility.rst:310
msgid ""
"DCS parsing is optional because fish temporarily switches to the alternate "
"screen before printing any DCS commands. However, since GNU screen neither "
"allows turning on the alternate screen buffer by default, nor treats DCS "
"commands in a compatible way, fish's initial prompt may be garbled by a DCS "
"payload like ``+q696e646e``. For the time being, fish works around this by "
"checking for presence of the :envvar:`STY` environment variable. If that "
"doesn't work for some reason, you can add this to your ``~/.screenrc``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../terminal-compatibility.rst:317
msgid "altscreen on"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../terminal-compatibility.rst:321
msgid "Or add this to your ``config.fish``::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../terminal-compatibility.rst:323
msgid ""
"function GNU-screen-workaround --on-event fish_prompt\n"
"    commandline -f repaint\n"
"    functions --erase GNU-screen-workaround\n"
"end"
msgstr ""

